Title: Object: Alexandria d'Egipto
Series: Diverse Viste delli Luoghie Contrade di Barbaria e il Stretto di Gibraltar
Description: Harbour scene in Alexandria; in the foreground, an ornate pillar at centre, a ship berthed to its left, figures walking; in the middle ground, the city of Alexandria, with El-Mursi Abul Abbas Mosque at right and the Citadel of Qaitbay at left; in the background, a mountainous landscape; early state. c.1665 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Lucas Vorsterman II (attributed)
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of eleven views of Gibraltar and various other sites in Africa, published by Jacob Peeters. For the full set see 2AA*,a.43.97-2AA*,a.43.107, for the comment on the entire set see 2AA*,a.43.97. See 2AA+,a.43.106 for later state.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (77.I) (Lucas Vorsterman)
Landwehr 1970 / Romeyn de Hooghe as book illustrator (82)
Acquisition notes: For comment on the likely provenance from Sloane, see Qq,6A.1.
